rest_of_day_open: I see my week going well, but very busy. I will be doing some work, finish taking this week-long class, and do some exercise interspersed throughout the week. I will be trying to eat healthy and drink a lot of water. I would like to finish up one assignment that's been bugging me for the past few months, and I'm only 1/3 of the way done.
critical_positive: I like how friendly both of us were and how open we were to our childhood. My partner was open about her relationship with her ex, and I was open about my family. We both smiled and talked a lot, with little interruption or pauses. I really enjoyed the talk.
critical_negative: There were no technical issues. We didn't have any problem finding topics to talk about. Both of us were of the same age group and yet we both experienced different lives as girls. There really wasn't anything negative. It was easy to get started and easy to end the chat.

rest_of_day_open: I will leave for a trip to Texas in 4 days. I will be packing and planning to meet with friends and family while I am there. The first person on my biological father's side of the family that I will meet will be my cousin, who we will be staying with. It will be interesting to see how well this goes.
critical_positive: We were able to relate to each other a lot and, especially considering we were fairly close in age and grew up in about the same time period, we were able to understand each others' references. There was probably about 8 years between us, judging by her reference to her 10 year high school reunion, but that is close enough to remember a lot of the same things growing up. It made our anecdotes ore intersting and entertaining.
critical_negative: We did interrupt each other a little, though not as bad as in previous conversations, and it was usually to interject an interesting or amusing comment. Also, we had a little bit of a slow start at the beginning of the conversation, but once we got going, the conversation picked itself up and seemed to move smoothly after that.
